    <h2>Japan's Fashion District</h2>
    <p class="description-2">Harajuku is known as Japan's fashion district, with quirky vintage clothing stores
        and cosplay shops along Takeshita Street, and traditional botiques on Omotesando Avenue. The word Harajuku
        means "meadow lodging" in Japanese. As a town, it's been around since at least the 12th century.</p>
    
